Tangent Space of Local Ring
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $(R,\mathfrak{m},\Bbbk)$
\end_inset

 be a local noetherain ring.
 Recall the tangent space of 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

 is defined to be the 
\begin_inset Formula $\Bbbk$
\end_inset

-vector space:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathrm{T}_{\mathfrak{m}}(R)=\mathrm{Hom}_{\Bbbk}(\mathfrak{m}\slash\mathfrak{m}^{2},\Bbbk).
\]

\end_inset

Recall that a 
\series bold
point-derivation 
\series default

\begin_inset Formula $\partial\colon R\to\Bbbk$
\end_inset

 is a 
\begin_inset Formula $\Bbbk$
\end_inset

-linear map which satisfies Leibniz law, meaning
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\partial(r_{1}r_{2})=\partial(r_{1})\overline{r}_{2}+\overline{r}_{1}\partial(r_{2})
\]

\end_inset

for all 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{1},r_{2}\in R$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $\overline{r}\in\Bbbk$
\end_inset

 denotes the image of 
\begin_inset Formula $r\in R$
\end_inset

 under the canonical quotient map 
\begin_inset Formula $R\twoheadrightarrow\Bbbk$
\end_inset

.
 The set of all point-derivations 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial\colon R\to\Bbbk$
\end_inset

 forms an 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-module and is given by
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathrm{Der}_{\Bbbk}(R,\Bbbk)=\mathrm{Hom}_{R}(\Omega_{R\slash\Bbbk},\Bbbk),
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega_{R\slash\Bbbk}$
\end_inset

 is the module of Kahler differentials of 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

 over 
\begin_inset Formula $\Bbbk$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

